<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  Raktify sitemap (static).

  RULE: only list pages we actually want indexed, and NEVER list a path
  that robots.txt Disallows. A URL that is both sitemap-listed AND
  robots-blocked shows up in Search Console as "Discovered - currently
  not indexed / Last crawled: N/A" (Google finds it via the sitemap but
  is then forbidden from crawling it). Keep the two files in sync.

  Deliberately EXCLUDED (auth / utility / robots-disallowed — do not add):
    /login              donor login form — no search value
    /staff/login        robots-disallowed (institutional auth)
    /onboarding/apply   robots-disallowed (B2B apply form)
    /admin, /donor, /bb, /hospital, /coordinator, /community-leader,
    /dho, /setup/*, /activate/*, /camp/*  — all robots-disallowed

  Per-community public pages (/community/:slug) are NOT listed here in
  v1 because the slug list is dynamic. Two future options:
    a) Backend endpoint /sitemap-communities.xml that lists active +
       public communities, referenced from this file via <sitemapindex>.
    b) Static-prerender + commit one entry per community.
  Both can land when community count is large enough to matter.
-->
